Gymshark Train
We train. We motivate. We grow. Together.
Step up your game and join the family, so we can #GymsharkTrain together 🦈

#Gymsharktrain

#Gymsharktrain

#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
Get ready to make that full body work with this powerful at-home HIIT workout from @mrandmrsmuscle 💪 
Tag a friend who you would duo this with!
#Gymsharktrain

Please only take part in the workout if you are medically and physically fit and have not been advised not to participate by a qualified medical professional. If your health or fitness changes adversely in any way before, during and/or after the workout please seek and follow medical advice without delay.

node.text:
@wozldn brings you a 🔥 full body workout to celebrate the last day of #Gymshark66! Expect 30 minutes of dynamic and energetic H.I.I.T exercises – you're defo going to need some water 🥵

Please only take part in the workout if you are medically and physically fit and have not been advised not to participate by a qualified medical professional. If your health or fitness changes adversely in any way before, during and/or after the workout please seek and follow medical advice without delay.

Want to increase your flexibility? Then try this mobility flow routine by @jessicaolie 🙌
Click the link in our bio for more mobility workouts‼️ #Gymsharktrain

node.text:
Boost your mood by taking your next workout outdoors. You won't regret it! 🌞
Be sure to use this boss @hxhails HIIT session when you get there:
1️⃣ Banded squat to side kick
2️⃣ Squat to kick back
3️⃣ Criss cross squat jumps
4️⃣ Squat jump w/ arm swing
Tag a gym buddy who would join you for this one 👭
#GymsharkTrain

node.text:
Swipe + save for a 🔥FIRE🔥 workout you can do at home or in the gym.
Workout:
🥵 Banded hip thrusts
🥵 Frog pumps
🥵 Lateral walks
🥵 Banded squats
Do each exercise for 40 seconds then rest 30-60 seconds. Repeat the same exercise for 4 sets before moving onto the next one.
📸: @jessicaolie 
#GymsharkTrain

node.accessibility_caption:
Alex Rice wears the Gymshark Ruched Training Sports Bra in dark green and Vital Seamless 2.0 shorts in dark green marl whilst performing a leg and glute workout.

The first exercise is goblet squats with a pulse, which she does for 3 sets, 8 reps each. 

The second is 3 sets of single leg, heel elevated glute bridges for 12 reps each leg. She holds a weight on the hip of her fixed leg. 

Exercise three is 4 sets of a pyramid set of sumo deadlifts, starting with 12 reps, then 10, then 8 and then 6. As she goes down in reps, the weight increases. 

The fourth exercise is Bulgarian split squats where she holds a dumbbell in each hand, either side of her leg. She does this for 3 sets, 8 reps per leg. 

Finally, she performs 3 sets of 1.5 dumbbell hip thrusts, for 10 reps.

node.text:
Who else is starting the week off with legs?!🦵
You've got to save + try this @alexricee routine if you are ✔️
1️⃣ Goblet squats w/ a pulse (3x8)
2️⃣ Single leg heels elevated glute bridge (3x12 each side)
3️⃣ Sumo deadlifts (4x12,10,8,6 increasing weight as you go down in reps)
4️⃣ Bulgarian split squat (3x8 each side)
5️⃣ DB hip thrusts (3x10)
#GymsharkTrain

node.accessibility_caption:
Isaiah Turner wears the Gymshark Arrival 5” shorts in blue whilst performing a HIIT workout at Oak Street Beach.

There are 4 exercises which he does back to back and then rests for 1-3 minutes. He does this for 3-5 rounds. The exercises are: high knees, mountain climbers, toe taps and squat jumps.

node.text:
Make your workout work anywhere with this outdoor HIIT session 🦈
1️⃣ High knees
2️⃣ Mountain climbers
3️⃣ Toe taps
4️⃣ Squat jumps
Perform each exercise for 30 seconds back-to-back, then rest for 1-3 mins. Complete 3-5 rounds.
Leave a comment with your fave training location so others can be inspired ⬇️
📸: @isaiah_fit30
#GymsharkTrain

node.text:
Make sure you're doing these essential #trailrunning pre-run stretches before you set off next ⚠️ 🏃
Watch the full video for instructions from @devonlevesque ✔️
#Gymsharktrain

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by @gymsharktrain on August 12, 2021 tagging @stevecook, @shaunstafford, @gymshark, @gymsharkwomen, and @gymsharktrain. May be an image of 2 people, biceps, people standing and indoor.

node.text:
Tag your training buddy and hype them up through this upper body workout 💪 💪
Follow along with @stevecook:
1️⃣ Dumbbell curls (12, 12, 12)
2️⃣ Hammer curls (10, 10, 10)
3️⃣ Spider curls (5, 5, 5)
+ Superset
4️⃣ Wide grip straight bar curls (as many as possible x 3 sets)
#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
If August is your month to get back into the gym, arrive prepared and ready to smash it with this guided workout from @yandz_x 🦈
1️⃣ Kneeling thruster (3x8-10)
2️⃣ Weighted push up (3x8-10)
3️⃣ Plate swing squat (3x8-10)
4️⃣ Plate hold bicycle (3x8-10)
Don't forget to tap save ✔️
#Gymsharktrain
